<HEAD>Co-Founder of `Systems Analysis' Dead At 79</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGUNA HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Schaumberg </PERSON> <PERSON> Quade </PERSON>, who helped develop the methodical problem-solving method known as systems analysis, died after suffering a stroke, the <ORGANIZATION> Rand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said. He was 79. <PERSON> Quade </PERSON>, who had cancer of the spine, died Saturday at <LOCATION> Saddleback </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> after suffering the stroke a week earlier, <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Weeks </PERSON>, spokesman for the <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Monica-based </LOCATION> think tank, said Monday. The <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, native, a consultant to Rand at the time of his death, joined the research group when it was founded in 1948 and retired in 1973. He and some colleagues devised and developed systems analysis as a recognized scientific discipline, Weeks said. <PERSON> Quade </PERSON>'s 1968 book, `` Systems Analysis and Policy Planning: Applications in Defense,'' defined systems analysis as `` a systematic approach to helping a decision-maker choose a course of action by investigating his full problem, searching out objectives and alternatives, and comparing them in the light of their consequences.'' <PERSON> Quade </PERSON> studied physics and mathematics at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Gainesville </LOCATION>, and earned his doctorate at <ORGANIZATION> Brown </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. After World War II service in the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>, he returned to the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION>, where he headed the math department until joining Rand. Survivors include his wife, <PERSON> Sylvia </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Laguna </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>, an