d released more than 100 Arab teen-agers from jail so they could attend classes. Schools had been closed since February and <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> officials said their reopening indicates a waning of the anti-occupation uprising, in which 202 Palestinians and two Israelis have been killed. <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> military government spokesman <PERSON> Olivier </PERSON> <PERSON> Rawofitz </PERSON> reported 90 percent attendance that he said showed a wish to return to normal life. But students vowed to stage protests after classes.
