l industry proposal for the advance rocket later this month, <PERSON> Berg </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> NASA </ORGANIZATION> plans to begin phasing in the advanced rocket in 1994 and that process is expected to take about four years, meaning <PERSON> Morton </PERSON> <PERSON> Thiokol </PERSON> will still be involved in providing the current shuttle rockets for years, <PERSON> Berg </PERSON> said. In addition, <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> plans to invest $ 200 million in coming years to modernize its northern <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION> plant in order to seek other space and defense business, <PERSON> Raab </PERSON> said. The company, which makes and sells chemicals, rockets and salt, intends to go after the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> advanced launch system, a strap-on booster and other contracts, he said.
